alaIpmsStatus.name: alaIpmsStatus
alaIpmsStatus.description: Administratively enables/disables IPMS on this switch.

alaIpmsLeaveTimeout.name: alaIpmsLeaveTimeout
alaIpmsLeaveTimeout.description: The IGMP Leave Timeout Interval in seconds.

alaIpmsQueryInterval.name: alaIpmsQueryInterval
alaIpmsQueryInterval.description: The IGMP Query interval in seconds.

alaIpmsNeighborTimer.name: alaIpmsNeighborTimer
alaIpmsNeighborTimer.description: The IPMS neighboring multicast router timeout interval in seconds.

alaIpmsQuerierTimer.name: alaIpmsQuerierTimer
alaIpmsQuerierTimer.description: The IPMS neighboring querier timeout interval in seconds.

alaIpmsMembershipTimer.name: alaIpmsMembershipTimer
alaIpmsMembershipTimer.description: The IGMP Group Membership timeout in seconds.

alaIpmsPriority.name: alaIpmsPriority
alaIpmsPriority.description: The traffic priority applied to all IP multicast flows.

alaIpmsMaxBandwidth.name: alaIpmsMaxBandwidth
alaIpmsMaxBandwidth.description: The maximum ingress IP multicast traffic forwarded for each Coronado of the switch. This value should be specified in megabits. Hardware platforms lacking support for this command will read 0.

alaIpmsHardwareRoute.name: alaIpmsHardwareRoute
alaIpmsHardwareRoute.description: Enable or disable hardware based routing for IPMS

alaIpmsIGMPMembershipProxyVersion.name: alaIpmsIGMPMembershipProxyVersion
alaIpmsIGMPMembershipProxyVersion.description: Set the default IGMP version for membership reports being proxied to external neighbors and queriers.

alaIpmsOtherQuerierTimer.name: alaIpmsOtherQuerierTimer
alaIpmsOtherQuerierTimer.description: The IGMP Other Querier timeout in seconds.

alaIpmsGroupTable.name: alaIpmsGroupTable
alaIpmsGroupTable.description: The Group table contains information about all ports that have requested membership in a multicast group.

alaIpmsGroupEntry.name: alaIpmsGroupEntry
alaIpmsGroupEntry.description: An entry corresponds to a membership request.

alaIpmsGroupDestIpAddr.name: alaIpmsGroupDestIpAddr
alaIpmsGroupDestIpAddr.description: The destination IP address of the membership request.

alaIpmsGroupClientIpAddr.name: alaIpmsGroupClientIpAddr
alaIpmsGroupClientIpAddr.description: The IP address of the last client requesting membership.

alaIpmsGroupClientMacAddr.name: alaIpmsGroupClientMacAddr
alaIpmsGroupClientMacAddr.description: The source MAC address of the membership request.

alaIpmsGroupClientVlan.name: alaIpmsGroupClientVlan
alaIpmsGroupClientVlan.description: The source VLAN of the membership request.

alaIpmsGroupClientIfIndex.name: alaIpmsGroupClientIfIndex
alaIpmsGroupClientIfIndex.description: The source ifIndex value of the membership request.

alaIpmsGroupClientVci.name: alaIpmsGroupClientVci
alaIpmsGroupClientVci.description: The source vci of the membership request.

alaIpmsGroupIGMPVersion.name: alaIpmsGroupIGMPVersion
alaIpmsGroupIGMPVersion.description: The IGMP version of the client.

alaIpmsGroupIGMPv3SrcIP.name: alaIpmsGroupIGMPv3SrcIP
alaIpmsGroupIGMPv3SrcIP.description: The IP address of the IGMPv3 requested source. The value 0.0.0.0 will be used for IGMPv3 exclude none, or IGMPv2 membership requests.

alaIpmsGroupIGMPv3SrcType.name: alaIpmsGroupIGMPv3SrcType
alaIpmsGroupIGMPv3SrcType.description: The type of the IGMPv3 required for this source.

alaIpmsGroupIGMPv3SrcTimeout.name: alaIpmsGroupIGMPv3SrcTimeout
alaIpmsGroupIGMPv3SrcTimeout.description: The timeout of the requested IGMPv3 source. This value is only applicable to include type sources, all others will be zero.

alaIpmsGroupTimeout.name: alaIpmsGroupTimeout
alaIpmsGroupTimeout.description: The timeout of the membership request. This field will always contain a valid timeout for IGMPv2 and IGMPv3 exclude clients. This value will be zero for IGMPv3 include clients.

alaIpmsNeighborTable.name: alaIpmsNeighborTable
alaIpmsNeighborTable.description: The Neighbor table contains information about all ports that link to multicast routers.

alaIpmsNeighborEntry.description: An entry corresponds to a multicast router.

alaIpmsNeighborIpAddr.name: alaIpmsNeighborIpAddr

alaIpmsNeighborIfIndex.name: alaIpmsNeighborIfIndex
alaIpmsNeighborIfIndex.description: The ifIndex value of the neighbor.

alaIpmsStaticNeighborRowStatus.description: Used in accordance to installation and removal conventions for conceptual rows. The RowStatus values that are supported are the following: active - The row is active and valid. createAndGo - The row will be created and activated. destroy - The row will be destroyed.
